article.headline: New Mexico State 79, Pacific 69 (OT)
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- New Mexico State scored the game's final 12 points to beat Pacific 79-69 in overtime Saturday, ending the Tigers' seven-game winning streak. Johnny Gray's 30-foot desperation 3-pointer at the regulation buzzer sent the game into an extra period tied 67-67, but Pacific (18-7) never scored again after Mike Webb made the first basket of overtime to give the Tigers their final lead. Tyrone Nelson had 21 points and nine rebounds to lead New Mexico State (12-12), which got 14 points from Ted Knauber and 13 from David Fisher. Christian Maraker scored a game-high 30 points and had eight rebounds for Pacific, the two-time defending Big West champion that hadn't lost since Jan. 15. Gray had 11 points for the Tigers and Webb scored 10. Elijah Ingram made four consecutive free throws in the final 39 seconds of regulation to give New Mexico State an apparently safe 67-64 lead, but the Aggies turned over the ball on an inbounds pass with 2.6 seconds remaining. After a timeout, Gray's heave from far beyond the top of the key tied the game for the 10th time and gave Pacific new life. But the Tigers committed four turnovers in overtime and New Mexico State took advantage. Fisher scored five consecutive points punctuated by a dunk in the game-ending 12-0 run. The game featured 23 lead changes, including 11 in the second half, when the two teams never were separated by more than four points in the final 18 minutes. New Mexico State moved ahead in the first half behind the inside play of Nelson and the outside shooting of Knauber. Nelson scored 11 first-half points and his jumper gave New Mexico State its biggest lead of the half at 34-26 with 2:20 to play. But Pacific responded with 3-pointers from Gray and Webb and a 3-point play from Maraker to take a 35-34 lead at the break.
